                          <p class="Para">The imbalance between demand and available resources, based on the forecast doubling of over 65s to about 40% of the populations of many nations will force radical changes in health and social care service delivery in the coming decades.</p>
                          <p class="Para">The creation of “Virtual Care Service Utilities” to coordinate and optimize use of scarce resources coupled with the extensive use of assistive technology systems is examined. The potential benefits are reviewed and weighed against the inherent loss of privacy involved, together with the trust building and change management implications of such a major rationalisation process.</p>
